article.description: Ashley Earley scored 22 points -- 12 straight in the second half -- as Vanderbilt defeated Troy 78-50 Sunday for its 48th straight nonconference homecourt victory.
article.headline: Earley scores 12 straight points in second half
article.linkText: Earley's 12 straight drive Vanderbilt past Troy
article.story:
NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Ashley Earley scored 12 straight points
in the second half and finished with 22, and Vanderbilt (No. 13 ESPN/USA Today; No. 15 AP)
defeated Troy 78-50 Sunday for its 48th straight home victory over
a nonconference opponent.

	   Carla Thomas finished with 15 points for Vanderbilt (11-1), Abi
Ramsey added 14 and Dee Davis scored 12.

	   Amy Lewis led Troy (2-7) with 17 points.

	   Vanderbilt broke the contest open midway through the first half,
scoring 11 straight points to extend a 17-10 lead to 28-10.

	   Troy ended the run on a 3-point basket by Laura Lee Holman with
6:35 remaining, the first of three straight 3s, but never got
closer than 15 points before the break.

	   The Commodores extended their lead to 39-19 on Ramsey's
3-pointer with 2:42 left in the half, but Audrey Muse scored a
minute later and Troy was with 18 points at the break.

	   With Vanderbilt leading 56-34, Earley went on her run. The
senior forward hit all six of her shots over a 5-minute span,
giving the Commodores a 68-44 lead at the 7:19 mark.

	   Vanderbilt took a 76-46 lead with three minutes remaining on a
3-pointer by Caroline Williams.
